---

## API Design Overview

This RESTful API manages the Smart Campus initiative, providing 
endpoints to manage physical Rooms and the Sensors deployed within 
them, along with a historical log of Sensor Readings.

### Resource Hierarchy

/api/v1
├── /                        ← Discovery (HATEOAS metadata)
├── /rooms                   ← Room collection
│   └── /{roomId}            ← Individual room
└── /sensors                 ← Sensor collection
    └── /{sensorId}
        └── /readings        ← Sub-resource: sensor reading history

### In-Memory Data Storage
All data is stored using ConcurrentHashMap (thread-safe) inside a 
singleton DataStore class. No database is used.

### Design Principles Applied
- Proper HTTP status codes (200, 201, 400, 403, 404, 409, 422, 500)
- JSON-only request/response bodies
- Resource nesting via JAX-RS Sub-Resource Locator pattern
- Centralised error handling via Exception Mappers
- Cross-cutting concerns (logging) via JAX-RS Filters

