## How to Build and Run

### Prerequisites
- Java 11 or above
- Apache Maven 3.6+
- Apache Tomcat 9.x
- NetBeans IDE 19+

### Step 1 - Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/wathmipadamarasi/SmartCampusAPI.git
cd SmartCampusAPI

### Step 2 - Open in NetBeans
1. Open NetBeans
2. File → Open Project
3. Browse to the SmartCampusAPI folder
4. Click Open Project

### Step 3 - Build the Project
Right-click the project → Clean and Build
OR run in terminal:
mvn clean package

### Step 4 - Run the Project
Right-click the project → Run
Tomcat will start automatically and deploy the WAR file.

### Step 5 - Verify
Open browser and visit:
http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1
You should see a JSON discovery response.

---

## Sample curl Commands

### 1. Discovery Endpoint
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1
Expected: 200 OK with API metadata and resource links.

### 2. Get All Rooms
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/rooms
Expected: 200 OK with list of all rooms.

### 3. Create a New Room
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/rooms \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"id":"ENG-205","name":"Engineering Lab","capacity":40}'
Expected: 201 Created with the new room object.

### 4. Create a New Sensor
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/sensors \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"id":"OCC-001","type":"Occupancy","status":"ACTIVE","currentValue":0,"roomId":"LIB-301"}'
Expected: 201 Created with the new sensor object.

### 5. Filter Sensors by Type
curl -X GET "http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/sensors?type=CO2"
Expected: 200 OK with only CO2 sensors.

### 6. Post a Sensor Reading
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/sensors/TEMP-001/readings \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"value":24.7}'
Expected: 201 Created. Also updates TEMP-001 currentValue to 24.7.

### 7. Get Reading History
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/sensors/TEMP-001/readings
Expected: 200 OK with list of all historical readings.

### 8. Delete Room with Sensors (409 Conflict)
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/rooms/LIB-301
Expected: 409 Conflict - room still has sensors assigned.

### 9. Create Sensor with Invalid roomId (422 Error)
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/sensors \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"id":"GAS-999","type":"Gas","status":"ACTIVE","currentValue":0,"roomId":"GHOST-ROOM"}'
Expected: 422 Unprocessable Entity.

### 10. Post Reading to MAINTENANCE Sensor (403 Forbidden)
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/sensors/TEMP-001/readings \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"value":99.9}'
Expected: 403 Forbidden.

